user_review: Wide selection of Sushi.  Note menu is in French, but anyone who knows sushi can figure it out.  I actually had to use Google to translate Saba.The restaurant seats about 20.  The sushi bar is clean and the chef is inviting.   Rolls are creative and very yummy.   There is a vegan roll that contains a deep fried imperial roll in the center... you must try that.  Its wrapped in avocado. The bathroom is only a unisex single,  but it's pretty big and clean.   They use the space to store their cleaning supplies.
Really disappointed with the quality of the sushi. It did not taste fresh and some pieces looked old.

Hidden gem! The presentation was gorgeous and the sushi was unique and fresh! Their original creations did not disappoint, and we even went back again in the same week because we couldn't get enough! Ambiance is similar to a sushi shop, so it's not the restaurants strong suit. Good sushi for a good price.

Omg it's so good here!!! The rice is perfectly seasoned and al dente. The flavours are fun and you get a ton of variety. Everything is fresh and and well prepared. The lunch menu is affordable and you can make it a combo as well. I had the 14 pieces that costs me roughly 12$ with tips and taxes included. I'm so glad I found this place. On the plus side, they also do delivery. I have a feeling that I'll be ordering a lot from them. Staff super nice and the place really clean. I'm not a big fan of nigiris and this place offers to substitute it with futomakies. How fun is that?!! I love it! Besides great sushi, they also have salads, soups, poke bowls, bentos... I mean, I just finished eating lunch and I'm already placing an order for dinner lol. Can you tell how excited I am about this place?

ATMOSPHERE: It's a pretty small restaurant. It can seat up to 15 people max. Seems to be more of a take-out style restaurant in my opinion. The inside is nice and modern. It's about a 3 minute walk from the metro so it's very convenient.FOOD: The food was very good! I had the salmon and tuna poke bowl. The ingredients were fresh and very tasty. The flavours merged well together and the bonito flakes mixed with rice was heavenly. It didn't fill me up but it was still yummy. The sushi looks promising as well. PRICE: I came here during their opening day so I was able to receive 50% off and it came up to 9$. Pretty worth it! Poke bowls range from 13-15$ with sides that are 1-2$ extra.SERVICE: The service was very good and quick. The cashier had a bit of difficulty speaking English but it wasn't a big deal at all.

They say "they call their food: traditional but modern". And it's true.I ate a Poké crab & shrimp, and it was FA BU LOUS !!! I highly recommand this place. Small, but very pleasant. Also the toiletts are very good.
Really fresh and I love their poke bowl. They do offer delivery\to go but just eat in the store if you have time.
Definitely amazing! I ordered the poke and sushi, both of them are perfect! It is better than furusato and I would be back again.
Sashimi 15 piece was just bad. Tiny pieces, awful value and marginal quality. Bad bad bad
Amazing small restaurant!The poke is obsoletely delicious! Very big size with cheap price. And the sushi is also good!

I've been to this place twice and I was satisfied both times! The sushis are prepared by the chef and evry pieces were fresh. It is not pricey at all. During lunch time, they have a lunch menu combo. I chose the 11 pieces and it cost me about 7$ which is really not bad!! The place is small, they have few tables but they keep it really clean! I would definitely return to this place and have more of those delicious sushis! Give it a try:)
It's worth it. Good value. We only had a midi menu, so I cannot talk about rest of menu. Place seems renewed. Around 10 tables. Looks clean.

This is probably the best sushi  place I've ever had in my entire life.  At first it seemed sketchy that it was four and a half stars and only 3 reviews, but the reviews are all correct, it is the best!!!!  The service is great and the bathroom is clean.  It is also perfectly priced.
